###########################################################################
#  sym_special - exercise @Sym for Greek letters and miscellaneous        #
#  special characters that map to the Symbol font in the PS output.       #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
Greek lowercase: @Sym alpha , @Sym beta , @Sym gamma , @Sym delta ,
@Sym epsilon , @Sym lambda , @Sym mu , @Sym pi , @Sym sigma , @Sym omega .

@PP
Greek uppercase: @Sym Gamma , @Sym Delta , @Sym Theta , @Sym Lambda ,
@Sym Sigma , @Sym Omega .

@PP
Mathematical: @Sym infinity , @Sym summation , @Sym product , @Sym integral ,
@Sym partialdiff , @Sym plusminus , @Sym lessequal , @Sym greaterequal ,
@Sym notequal , @Sym approxequal .

@PP
Inline form: the area of a circle is @Sym pi r and the limit as
@Sym epsilon @Sym arrowright 0 .

@End @Text
